Releases are done at GitHub

build and distribute with:

```
    github-release upload -u jmn --repo goodreads --tag 0.2 --name "goodreads-linux-amd64" --file gr.bz2
```
1. Set GITHUB_TOKEN environment flag
2. # make your tag and upload
   $ git tag 0.XX && git push --tags

# create a formal release
$ github-release release \
    --user aktau \
    --repo gofinance \
    --tag v0.1.0 \
    --name "the wolf of source street" \
    --description "Not a movie, contrary to popular opinion. Still, my first release!" \
    --pre-release


# upload a file, for example the OSX/AMD64 binary of my gofinance app
$ github-release upload \
    -u jmn \
    --repo goodreds \
    --tag 0.XX \
    --name "gofinance-osx-amd64" \
    --file bin/darwin/amd64/gofinance

# upload other files...
$ github-release upload ...

All from: https://github.com/aktau/github-release
